---
import SectionLabel from "./SectionLabel.astro";
---

<section id="about" class="px-6 py-20 sm:px-10 sm:py-24">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-[72rem]">
    <SectionLabel number="01" label="About" />

    <h2
      class="mt-3 max-w-3xl font-light tracking-tight text-text"
      style="font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 3vw, 2.5rem);"
    >
      Engineer-first, with the analytics depth to back it up.
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-10 grid items-start gap-10 md:grid-cols-[240px_1fr]">
      <div>
        <div
          class="overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-border-strong bg-bg-elev shadow-[0_8px_30px_-12px_rgba(0,0,0,0.6)]"
          style="transform: rotate(-1deg);"
        >
          <picture>
            <source srcset="/avatar.png" type="image/png" />
            <source srcset="/avatar.jpg" type="image/jpeg" />
            <img
              src="/avatar.svg"
              alt="Tyler Dobson"
              width="240"
              height="240"
              loading="lazy"
              class="block h-auto w-full"
            />
          </picture>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <p class="text-base leading-relaxed text-text-dim sm:text-lg">
          I'm a junior at the University of South Florida studying Artificial Intelligence,
          Business Analytics &amp; Information Systems. I build AI-powered systems that turn
          manual workflows into automated infrastructure — and I back that with the kind of
          analytics discipline that turns raw data into structured business insights. Twelve-plus
          end-to-end portfolio projects so far, spanning Python, SQL, Tableau, Streamlit, ETL
          pipelines, and AI-assisted automation.
        </p>

        <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-text-dim sm:text-lg">
          Outside the repo, I support beverage operations for events with 15,000–20,000+
          attendees at Oak View Group and Legends Global — which is where I learned that
          operational scale, not code quality, is what breaks first under pressure. I'm
          currently learning AI engineering practices in public via real projects: prompt
          design, tool orchestration, validation loops, and human-in-the-loop review.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
